President Obama has announced his intention to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Linda Etim is being nominated as a member of the Board of Directors for the African Development Foundation. Lisa M. Fairfax is being nominated as a Commissioner for the Securities and Exchange Commission. Jean Elizabeth Manes is being nominated as the Ambassador to the Republic of El Salvador, and Scot Alan Marciel is being nominated as the Ambassador to the Union of Burma. Lastly, Linda Swartz Taglialatela is being nominated as the Ambassador to Barbados, the Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis, Saint Lucia, Antigua and Barbuda, the Commonwealth of Dominica, Grenada, and Saint Vincent and the Grenadines. President Obama expressed his gratitude for their willingness to serve the country and looks forward to working with them.